⟦ TEST: typed FFI accepts named product types via canonical normalization ⟧

⟦ Define the options type (must come before extern that references it) ⟧
t MkdirOptions={recursive:Bool}

⟦ Typed extern with record type parameter ⟧
e fs::promises:{
  mkdir:λ(String,MkdirOptions)=>Unit
}

⟦ Create typed options using the named product type; the checker normalizes it ⟧
c opts=({recursive:true}:MkdirOptions)

⟦ Now this typechecks! ⟧
λensureDir(dir:String)=>Unit=fs::promises.mkdir(dir, opts)

λmain()=>Unit=()
